==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Colonize
<hw>Col"o*nize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Colonized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Colonizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>coloniser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To plant or establish a colony or
colonies in; to people with colonists; to migrate to and settle
in.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They that would thus <qex>colonize</qex> the stars with
inhabitants.</q> <rj><qau>Howell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colonize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Colonize
<hw>Col"o*nize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To remove to, and settle in,
a distant country; to make a colony.</def> <rj><au>C.
Buchanan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>colonized</ent>⟦br⟧
